{
  "text": "Davidson and colleagues [CITATION_1] utilized targeted sequencing of the IL23R gene to identify rare polymorphisms associated with ankylosing spondylitis in a Han Chinese population. Targeted sequencing of a 170 kb region containing IL23R and its flanking regions was performed in 100 Han Chinese subjects and again in 1,950 subjects of European descent and identified several potentially functional rare variants, including a non-synonymous risk variant (G149R) that proved to be associated with the disease.",
